        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Provide the package entry point for line feature extractors — modules that compute discriminative features from document lines for downstream classification. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Package initialization for feature_extractors subpackage. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (package-level). \par \b Output\/ \:  Public symbols re-exported from feature extractor modules. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(8): <ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1data__structures" kindref="compound">dedoc.data_structures</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>All feature extractors produce a consistent feature vector per line. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why separate features into their own package? A: Feature computation is a distinct concern from classification; modular features enable composition and reuse across classifiers. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
